al transform perhaps second only to the Fourier transform in its utility in=
 solving physical problems. The Laplace transform is particularly useful in=
 solving linear ordinary differential equations such as those arising in th=
e analysis of electronic circuits. The (unilateral) Laplace transform L (no=
t to be confused with the Lie derivative, also commonly denoted L) is defin=
ed by  L_t[f(t)](s)=3Dint_0^inftyf(t)e^(-st)dt,  (1)   where f(t) is define=
d for t&gt;=3D0...">
